videos.headline: Rypien fumble gives Fresno State great field position
videos.description: With the rain pouring down, Boise State QB Brett Rypien awkwardly fumbles the ball and it is recovered by Fresno State's Mykal Walker.

videos.headline: McMaryion hits Quick for the 15-yard TD
videos.description: Marcus McMaryion connects with Michiah Quick on the corner throw for a 15-yard touchdown and a Fresno State 7-0 lead.

videos.headline: Modster extends and drags the toe for a 10-yard TD
videos.description: Boise State's Sean Modster hauls in a shoe-string 10-yard touchdown to tie the game at 7-7.

videos.headline: Mattison  dives in for the 34-yard TD
videos.description: Boise State's Alexander Mattison finds the hole, hops through the tackle and dives in for the 34-yard touchdown to tie the game at 13-13.

videos.headline: Rivers  1-yard TD seals Mountain West title
videos.description: Ronnie Rivers beats his defender and turns the corner for a 1-yard touchdown to give Fresno State a 19-13 OT win and the Mountain West Championship.
